    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Wmsport</placeName>
                <date>Sept 3d 1865</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dr Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I <sic>recieved</sic> those<lb/> Sabbath School books, and
                enclose<lb/> the amount for the same. The<lb/> children seem to be quite
                interested<lb/> in the new Sunday School, and I hope<lb/> in time it may have the
                desired effect<lb/> of arousing the parents to a sense of<lb/> their duty! Many
                thanks for the<lb/> advice, and also for your kindness<lb/> in forwarding those
                books.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Have you any other books for <date>Sabbath</date></p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>reading for children, in the<lb/>
                <placeName>Philad</placeName> Sunday school, little <sic>stroy</sic><lb/> books for
                home reading? I think<lb/> they would be needed, something to induce<lb/> a
                continued attention even in little children<lb/> Those Occidents have not arrived
                yet.<lb/> Father &amp; Mother join in sending best<lb/> wishes to you</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">truly yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Amelia E. Ulman</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
